HEADWORD: Pelta
<hw>Pel"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pelt⟦ae⟧</plw>.</plu> <ety>[L., a shield, fr. Gr.
<grk>pe`lth</grk>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Antiq.)</fld> <def>A small
shield, especially one of an approximately elliptic form, or
crescent-shaped.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A flat apothecium having no
rim.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

